This paper discusses a method for optimizing large scale machine learning models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sparse matrix multiplications, which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves the computation of gradients, which is a fundamental concept in optimization (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of the algorithm on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well.
